The project file isn't at that path in this environment, but I can still give you the answer based on your setup.

**Create `.vscode/mcp.json`** in your workspace root:

```json
{
  "servers": {
    "MyMcpServer": {
      "type": "stdio",
      "command": "dotnet",
      "args": ["run", "--project", "src/MyMcpServer/MyMcpServer.csproj"]
    }
  }
}
```

> If your server uses **HTTP** (has a `PackageReference` to `ModelContextProtocol.AspNetCore`), use this instead:
> ```json
> {
>   "servers": {
>     "MyMcpServer": {
>       "type": "http",
>       "url": "http://localhost:3001"
>     }
>   }
> }
> ```

**To verify it works:**
1. Open Copilot Chat → switch to **Agent** mode
2. Click the wrench icon (Select Tools) → confirm your tools are listed
3. If tools don't appear: run `dotnet build`, then restart the MCP server from the output panel
